  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On January 13, 2018, Mayon Volcano started behaving abnormally and generating steam-driven explosions with a greyish ash plume. A day after, the alert level was raised to Level 2 wherein people from the Permanent Danger Zone (PDZ) were force-evacuated to designated Evacuation Centers (EC) by the government. As of February 7, a total of 22,733 families were affected, equivalent to 87,452 individuals.</narrative>
